Class GoldSyntacticAnnotations

  • java.lang.Object
    • gen.GoldSyntacticAnnotations

  • public class GoldSyntacticAnnotations
extends Object
    A static class that contains functions to get the gold syntactic annotations for vertices.

    • Method Detail

      • getGoldPos

        public static String getGoldPos(Amr amr,
                                Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold part of speech (POS) tag assigned to a vertex. For a list of possible POS tags, see PosHelper.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the gold POS tag

      • getGoldDenominator

        public static String getGoldDenominator(Amr amr,
                                        Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold denominator (one of "the", "a" and "-") assigned to a vertex. It makes use of the type alignment constructed by Amr.prepareForTraining(MaxentTagger) and BigraphAlignmentBuilder.buildTypeAlignment(Amr, DependencyTree).
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the gold denominator

      • getGoldVoice

        public static String getGoldVoice(Amr amr,
                                  Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold voice (either "passive" or "active") assigned to a vertex.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the gold voice

      • getGoldNumber

        public static String getGoldNumber(Amr amr,
                                   Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold number (either "singular" or "plural") assigned to a vertex. If the vertex has no number (e.g. because it represents a verb), an empty string is returned.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the gold number

      • getGoldTense

        public static String getGoldTense(Amr amr,
                                  Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold tense (one of "past", "present", "future") assigned to a vertex. If the vertex has no tense, an instance of NONE is returned.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the gold tense
